Former White House aide KennethDuberstein has been chosen to be President Reagan's deputychief of staff, administration officials said.    Duberstein, who is now a Washington lobbyist, previouslyserved in the Reagan White House as head of the president'scongressional liaison team.    As top assistant to White House chief of staff HowardBaker, he will handle administrative chores and serve as acontact point between the White House and Congress, officialstold Reuters. Reuter&#3;